Yay! Another pawn drop, an opponent's attacking Knight in great position, and complete loss of the center. It does make for an interesting development game, however.

See what I mean? Interesting game.
9. d3 fxe4 
10. Bg5 Nf6 
11. Ne5 exd3 
12. Bf7+ Ke7 
13. Bxf6+ gxf6 
14. Nxc6+ 
Black doesn't necessarily drop his queen, not even close, but you get how d3 could be a scary positional gambit.
